TASK_TITLE=Unify CLI: route doey-ctl commands through doey
TASK_STATUS=pending_user_confirmation
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_CREATED_BY=boss
TASK_TEAM=W2
TASK_DESCRIPTION=CATEGORY: deep

doey-ctl is the core implementation, but agents should only need to use 'doey' as the single CLI entry point. Two changes needed:

1. In doey.sh (the main CLI), add passthrough routing for doey-ctl subcommands: msg, status, nudge, and any other doey-ctl commands. When a user runs 'doey msg send ...' it should delegate to 'doey-ctl msg send ...'.

2. Update ALL agent .md files (and .md.tmpl templates where applicable) to replace 'doey-ctl' references with 'doey'. Remember: edit .md.tmpl templates, not generated .md files, then run expand-templates.sh.

The doey-ctl binary stays — doey just wraps it.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:W2.1: Add passthrough routing in doey.sh for doey-ctl subcommands (msg, status, nudge, etc.):done\n2:W2.2: Update all .md.tmpl templates, skills, and hooks to replace doey-ctl with doey:done
